{{Main|Fresno State Bulldogs}}
Since 1992, Fresno State has been competing in the [[Western Athletic Conference]]. The school's 16 varsity sports teams are known as the Bulldogs, and the school's colors are [[cardinal red (color)|red]] and [[blue]]. The Bulldogs have earned two [[NCAA]] national championships: one baseball title in 2008 and one softball title in 1998.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ncaa.org/champadmin/champs_listing1.html|title=How many NCAA Division I championships has your school won?}}</ref>
